title: Distribution of gross domestic product ( GDP ) across economic sectors in the Netherlands
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 3 lines representing Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis denotes Distribution of GDP in percentage and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Services is gradually increasing, Industry is gradually decreasing, Agriculture is roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Distribution of GDP in percentage in descending order is: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Overall across the Year, Services mostly maintained the highest Distribution of GDP in percentage when compared to others with a mean value of 68.97, and it peaked at 2016.
Followed by Industry which ranks as the second topmpost line , with an average of 19.1 Distribution of GDP in percentage,reaching its highest point  at 2008 with a value of 21.6.
The botommost line, Agriculture,  has a mean of 1.69, and peaked at 2017.
